{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/videos/recipes/chinese-bbq-pork-cha-siu","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>This cha siu recipe is near and dear to my heart.  It was my mom's recipe and over the years, she had pretty much perfected it to the perfect barbequed meat.</p>\n<p>You'll see from the photos that it is not your typical cha siu you get at a Chinese fast food restaurant.  Those are colored with red food coloring to mimic the effects of long roasting with fragrant flavorings like soy sauce, brown sugar and chu hou paste.</p>\n<p>The roasting only takes about an hour, but it bears a true likeness to a proper piece of barbequed meat - Chinese style.  Two ingredients you should look out for is rose wine and chu hou paste, both essential in making cha siu. Rose wine is distilled from sorghum along with rose petals, and it really adds to the flavor.  Chu hou paste is made from fermented soybeans and spices, and it's a major contributor to the cha siu's flavor and color.</p>\n<figure class=\"half\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 985px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/f7e6d267e448cd49a798668c0cfd9150/47362/193-4.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.7005076142132%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"193 4\" title=\"193 4\" src=\"/static/f7e6d267e448cd49a798668c0cfd9150/47362/193-4.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/f7e6d267e448cd49a798668c0cfd9150/90185/193-4.jpg 450w,\n/static/f7e6d267e448cd49a798668c0cfd9150/7288a/193-4.jpg 900w,\n/static/f7e6d267e448cd49a798668c0cfd9150/47362/193-4.jpg 985w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 985px) 100vw, 985px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 985px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/546b6b1f77cc13233fe247c159a9b9d7/47362/193-3.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.7005076142132%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"193 3\" title=\"193 3\" src=\"/static/546b6b1f77cc13233fe247c159a9b9d7/47362/193-3.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/546b6b1f77cc13233fe247c159a9b9d7/90185/193-3.jpg 450w,\n/static/546b6b1f77cc13233fe247c159a9b9d7/7288a/193-3.jpg 900w,\n/static/546b6b1f77cc13233fe247c159a9b9d7/47362/193-3.jpg 985w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 985px) 100vw, 985px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n</figure>\n<figure> \n   <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 985px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/a669a90f2defd7ba8619a542116c5b0e/47362/193-2.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.7005076142132%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"193 2\" title=\"193 2\" src=\"/static/a669a90f2defd7ba8619a542116c5b0e/47362/193-2.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/a669a90f2defd7ba8619a542116c5b0e/90185/193-2.jpg 450w,\n/static/a669a90f2defd7ba8619a542116c5b0e/7288a/193-2.jpg 900w,\n/static/a669a90f2defd7ba8619a542116c5b0e/47362/193-2.jpg 985w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 985px) 100vw, 985px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n</figure>\n<figure class=\"ingredients\" markdown=\"1\">\n<h3 id=\"chinese-bbq-cha-siu-recipe\"><a href=\"#chinese-bbq-cha-siu-recipe\" aria-label=\"chinese bbq cha siu recipe permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Chinese BBQ Cha Siu Recipe</h3>\n<p>(Makes 1-1.5-lbs cha siu)</p>\n<p>Pork:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 1-lb pork shoulder</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Marinade:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 teaspoon curry powder</li>\n<li>2 tablespoons brown sugar</li>\n<li>1 pinch pepper</li>\n<li>1 teaspoon garlic</li>\n<li>1 teaspoon ginger juice</li>\n<li>1 tablespoon rose wine</li>\n<li>1 teaspoon light soy</li>\n<li>2 teaspoons dark soy</li>\n<li>1 teaspoon sesame oil</li>\n<li>1 tablespoon chu hou sauce</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Basting Mixture:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>2 tablespoons ketchup</li>\n<li>1 tablespoon honey</li>\n<li>dash sugar</li>\n<li>1 teaspoon chu hou paste</li>\n</ul>\n</figure>\n<figure class=\"directions\" markdown=\"1\">\n<h3 id=\"directions\"><a href=\"#directions\" aria-label=\"directions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Directions</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Mix together the marinade ingredients until smooth. </li>\n<li>In a ziplock bag, place pork and marinade together.  Refrigerate for 4 hours or up to a day.</li>\n<li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.</li>\n<li>Place pork on a sheet pan lined with aluminum foil. Bake for 30 minutes.</li>\n<li>With a brush, baste pork on both sides.  Bake for an additional 20 minutes and baste again.</li>\n<li>Turn oven to broil.  Broil meat for an additional 6-7 minutes, until crust browns slightly.</li>\n<li>Cool and let rest for 15 minutes.  Slice to serve.</li>\n</ol>\n</figure>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"This cha siu recipe is near and dear to my heart.  It was my mom's recipe and over the years, she had pretty much perfected it to theâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Chinese BBQ Pork Cha Siu","image":{"feature":{"publicURL":"/static/193-1-db4c5320e90ff2f314a5c13eb2aeb14e.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.4992389649923896,"src":"/static/db4c5320e90ff2f314a5c13eb2aeb14e/b17c1/193-1.jpg","srcSet":"/static/db4c5320e90ff2f314a5c13eb2aeb14e/00e5e/193-1.jpg 200w,\n/static/db4c5320e90ff2f314a5c13eb2aeb14e/1a903/193-1.jpg 400w,\n/static/db4c5320e90ff2f314a5c13eb2aeb14e/b17c1/193-1.jpg 800w,\n/static/db4c5320e90ff2f314a5c13eb2aeb14e/df0bb/193-1.jpg 985w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"feature_video":"https://www.youtube.com/embed/jZkw2vzopxY?rel=0","date":"2016-03-21","categories":["videos","recipes"],"tags":["videos","cha siu","meats","pork","chinese bbq","bbq"]},"fields":{"slug":"/videos/recipes/chinese-bbq-pork-cha-siu","date":"2016-03-21T00:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/videos/recipes/chinese-bbq-pork-cha-siu","nextslug":"/videos/blog/boston-public-market-tour","prevslug":"/videos/recipes/the-ultimate-flakey-pie-crust"}}}